preventing failure to launch is service a path to purpose stanford center on adolescence jump to navigation s tanford c enter on a dolescence stanford university home overview people faculty and staff students visitors faculty members and affiliates activities research publications journal articles books chapters in book dissertations public presentations colloquia events conferences awards practice contact home activities public presentations preventing failure to launch is service a path to purpose preventing failure to launch is service a path to purpose authors william damon publication name or publisher damon discussed his recently published book the path to purpose which takes readers inside the minds of disengaged and drifting kids and exposes the depth of their confusion and anxiety about what they should do with their lives he tells us that our emphasis on superficial short term success is creating a generation of young people who lack confidence and direction as they try to define their futures he then talks to some inspired young people who are thriving and identifies nine key factors that have made the difference for them the key ingredient for the highly engaged is that they have developed a clear sense of purpose in their lives that motivates them and gives them direction audio and video media clips of this talk are available here presented at may 15 2008 bradley center for philanthropy and civic renewal activities research publications journal articles books chapters in books dissertations other public presentations colloquia events conferences awards practice 2011 stanford center on adolescence 505 lasuen mall stanford ca 94305 3083 office 650.725 8205 fax 650.725 8207
